BadgerBlitz.com, 251273=Buckeyes out to bowl over SEC - finally — 1/3/2011, from Rivals.com College Football, 266544=Notes: Parade All-American, Ohio's Mr. Football and one of the fastest sprinters in the state's history. In addition to winning a football title as a senior, won four career state track championships with personal bests of 10.38 seconds (state record) in the 100 meters and 6.79 in the 60. As a true freshman in 2007, played in 11 games and carried 60 times for 267 yards (4.5-yard average) and two touchdowns. Also caught 12 balls for 160 yards (13.3) with a touchdown and returned three kickoffs for 60 yards (20.0). Had arthroscopic surgery on his left knee in September and missed two games. A hamstring pull suffered in '08 fall camp set him back, as he slid down the depth chart and managed 26-65-1 (2.5) rushing with 3-37-0 (12.3) receiving and 8-141 (17.6) on kickoff returns in 12 games (did not play against Texas). In '09, played all 13 games, starting the final nine, and produced 145-739-4 (5.1) rushing, 17-224-2 (13.2) receiving and 4-83 (20.8) returning kickoffs. Suffered a mild concussion against Minnesota. Started 8-of-13 games in '10, totaling 70-337-2 (4.8) rushing and 23-195-5 (8.5) receiving. Team captain.
